      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl5",
      "rationale": "CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2024R1) operates under ISO 9001-certified QMS with full revision control, automated regression test suite covering 1200+ cases, and traceable build verification records. SQA documentation reviewed and found compliant with MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the Navier-Stokes and power-law hemolysis transport equations. Observed order of accuracy 1.97 (expected 2.0 for second-order scheme) confirmed within 2% tolerance across three systematically refined meshes. Code verification report archived at DOI 10.1115/vv40-codeverif-2025."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 11.8M, 31.5M cells). Grid Convergence Index for hemolysis index QoI is 2.1%, well within the 5% acceptance threshold. Temporal discretization verified with three time-step refinements; GCI_time = 0.8%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, blood analog fluid properties, temperature) are documented with calibrated instrumentation traceable to NIST standards. All five operating points replicated within ±1.5% of target conditions. Environmental conditions (temperature 37±0.5°C, hematocrit 35±1%) recorded for each test run."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison using ASME V&V 20 metric framework. Validation uncertainty Uval = 4.8% of mean hemolysis index; model error E = 3.2% at worst-case operating point. All five operating points fall within validation uncertainty bounds. Area validation metric computed for full velocity field comparison: Av = 0.92 (threshold 0.85). Blind prediction exercise conducted prior to experimental data release confirmed predictive capability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) directly corresponding to the clinical acceptance threshold. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time histogram) are mechanistically linked to hemolysis prediction. Clinical subject matter expert panel confirmed QoI relevance to patient safety decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — identical to the device COU geometry. Fluid properties matched to clinical operating conditions using porcine blood and glycerol-water blood analog. Operating envelope of validation experiments fully encompasses the COU operating range. Applicability analysis documented per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence verified to residual tolerance 1e-6 for all equations. Mass imbalance < 0.01% across all operating points. Round-off error assessed via double-precision arithmetic verification; negligible relative to discretization error. Solver error budget documented as <0.3% contribution to total numerical uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow executed under documented standard operating procedures with independent peer review of model setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing scripts. Two-analyst cross-check performed on all five operating point setups. Automated workflow scripts version-controlled and tested to prevent manual transcription errors."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) justified by systematic comparison of five turbulence models against PIV data at all operating points; SST k-omega demonstrated lowest RMS velocity error (4.1%). Power-law hemolysis model selected following literature survey of six candidate models; chosen model demonstrated best predictive performance across independent validation datasets. Model form uncertainty estimated via multi-model ensemble and incorporated into total uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed with 500 Latin hypercube samples propagating uncertainty in blood viscosity (±5%), hemolysis model coefficients (±10%), inlet velocity profile (±3%), and rotational speed (±0.5%). Total hemolysis index uncertainty at 95% confidence: ±6.2%. All input distributions documented with traceability to measurement data and literature sources."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements obtained from n=5 independent test runs per operating point using fresh porcine blood from three separate donors, providing biological variability characterization. Sample preparation protocol standardized and documented. Statistical analysis confirms inter-run repeatability CV < 8% and inter-donor variability CV < 12%, both within acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Systematic equivalency analysis performed mapping validation experiment input parameters to COU input parameters. Dimensionless similarity parameters (Reynolds number, flow coefficient, head coefficient) confirmed equivalent within ±2% across all five operating points. Geometric fidelity verified by CMM measurement of test article confirming dimensional tolerances within ±50 microns of nominal CAD geometry used in simulation."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-panel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels for Model Risk Level 5. Software quality assurance, numerical code verification, and discretization error assessments confirm the computational foundation is sound, with GCI values below 5% thresholds and observed convergence orders consistent with theoretical expectations. Validation activities demonstrate quantitative agreement between CFD predictions and experimental hemolysis measurements within the validation uncertainty bounds (Uval = 4.8%) at all five COU operating points. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification with 500 samples propagating all major input uncertainties yields a 95% confidence interval of ±6.2% on the hemolysis index, which remains below the clinical acceptance threshold with margin. Model form uncertainty was systematically characterized through multi-model ensemble analysis. Test conditions, test samples, and input parameter equivalency assessments confirm the validation evidence is directly applicable to the COU. The structured evidence chain from foundational experimental data through validation results to this credibility assessment is complete and traceable. The credibility assessment panel unanimously accepts this model for the intended use of predicting absolute hemolysis levels for regulatory submission supporting the Class III VAD device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
